item.title: NASA's Golden Age of Design Chronicled in Reissued Standards Manual
item.description:
NASA's Golden Age of Design Chronicled in Reissued Standards Manual

Last year, two graphic designers launched a wildly successful Kickstarter campaign to bring back the 1974 NASA Graphics Standards Manual as a hard cover book. Now, they're releasing the book to the public.

item.title: The Impossible Project Created a Brand New Camera For Its Resurrected Polaroid Film
item.description:
The Impossible Project Created a Brand New Camera For Its Resurrected Polaroid Film

After successfully bringing Polaroid 600 instant film back from the dead, the people behind the Impossible Project realized that hunting down a working Polaroid camera for the film wasn't always easy, so they've designed their own. Except this isn't your parent's Polaroid.
